Linear Modelling of Teams (Avg. Goals Conceded)

Initial assumption: Teams which are only represented a few times are replaced by new teams with same level next season.

Load libraries

library(boot)
library(tidyverse)
library(broom)

Load data

df <- read.csv('grand_total_df.csv')

Show data

head(df)

Pick out needed non-nominal variables Points and goals are removed as they effectively consist of other variables in the data

df <- df %>% 
      select(-X, -home_team_name, -season_home, -avg_total_goals, 
            -avg_goals_conceded_home, -avg_goals_conceded_away, -target_variable,
            -home_points, -away_points)

Fit linear model

model1 <- lm(avg_total_goals_conceded ~ .,
             data = df)

BOOTSTRAPPING (1) 
bs <- function(formula, data, indices){
  d <- data[indices, ] #allows boot to select sample
  fit <- lm(formula, data = d)
  return(coef(fit))
}
#Bootstrapping with 5000 replications
set.seed(200)
results <- boot(df, 
                statistic = bs,
                R = 5000,
                formula = formula(model1))

Plot distributions

for(i in 1:length(results$t0)){
  hist(results$t[,i], 
       freq = TRUE,
       main = variable.names(model1)[i])
}

Coefficients where histograms from bootstrapping are centered around 0 show lack of significance.

Coefficients clearly centered around 0: home_shotoff home_fouls home_r away_team_goal away_y2 away_poss away_corners away_r
